Title: EyesOff: How I Built A Screen Contact Detection Model
Description: I trained a model for my app EyesOff, which detects when people are looking at your screen to protect you from shoulder surfing. With no existing dataset for this task, I hand-labelled 20k+ images for training and created synthetic gaze labels for pre-training. The final model achieves ~71% accuracy across close and mid-range distances.
